gold_hypo: In this dataset, higher ADNC scores are observed to be associated with higher Braak stages.
In this dataset, APOE4 allele is observed to be more frequent in donors with high ADNC compared to those with lower or no ADNC.
In this dataset, individuals with high ADNC scores are observed to have a higher median age at death compared to those with low ADNC.
In this dataset, donors with higher ADNC scores are observed to exhibit later Thal phases.
In this dataset, as ADNC scores increase, CERAD scores are observed to also rise.
In this dataset, donors with high ADNC scores are observed to be diagnosed with dementia prior to death in higher proportion relative to donors assigned other ADNC scores.
In this dataset, higher ADNC scores are observed to show a higher incidence of comorbid neuropathologies.
In the RHP region, the subclass 019 L2/3 IT PPP Glut is the most prevalent with 2,394 occurrences.
In the observed data, class '19 MB Glut' includes 116 unique supertypes.
In the observed data, '24 MY Glut' includes 76 unique supertypes.

In the observed data, 'Glut' neurotransmitter class shows the following genotype distribution: 194,986 cells with Snap25-IRES2-Cre/wt;Ai14(RCL-tdT)/wt, 8,229 cells with Ai14(RCL-tdT)/wt, 1,861 cells with Slc32a1-IRES-Cre/wt;Ai14(RCL-tdT)/wt, 223 cells with Gad2-IRES-Cre/wt;Ai14(RCL-tdT)/wt, and 65 cells with wt/wt.

62 neuronal clusters exhibit dual glutamate-GABA co-transmission.
79 % of all clusters express at least one neuropeptide gene.
35 of the dopaminergic clusters co-release another fast transmitter.
24 of the 48 cholinergic clusters co-release glutamate.
7 of the 48 cholinergic clusters co-release GABA.
3 of the 48 cholinergic clusters co-release both glutamate and GABA.
1 of the 48 cholinergic clusters co-releases dopamine.
